Petrus Bekker

Pirow Bekker



Vice President, Medical and Clinical Affairs, Chemocentryx, Inc.




San Carlos, CA




Find other people named Petrus Bekker




General Info


Research and Development in the Physical, Engineering, and Life Sciences



Add Tags— eg, Finance, Business2Business...



Petrus (Pirow) Bekker, M.D., Ph.D.
Vice President, Medical and Clinical Affairs
 Dr. Bekker brings more than fifteen years of clinical development expertise. Prior to joining ChemoCentryx, Dr. Bekker was Senior Director of Global Safety for Amgen, overseeing all aspects of product safety worldwide, and also served as Senior Director of Clinical Development and Director of Clinical Development, where he was responsible for programs in inflammation, bone metabolism and neurology programs at all stages of development from preclinical to post-marketing. While at Amgen, Dr. Bekker led the development and facilitated the approvals of several Amgen products, including Enbrel®and Kineret®and contributed to the evaluation of in-licensing candidates for the company. 
Previous to his tenure at Amgen, Dr. Bekker spent nearly seven years at Procter & Gamble Pharmaceuticals where he played a key role in the clinical development of the osteoporosis drug Actonel®. 
Dr. Bekker received his medical training in his native South Africa, and his Ph.D. in molecular biology from Penn State University.


