                                                    ChemoCentryx to Hold Second Quarter 2017 Financial Results Conference Call on Tuesday, August 8, 2017
                                                


                                                    GlobeNewswire – 
                                                    8:30 AM ET 07/26/2017
                                                


ChemoCentryx, Inc. (CCXI), a biopharmaceutical company developing new medications targeted at inflammatory and autoimmune diseases and cancer, today announced that the Company's second quarter 2017 financial results will be released after market close on Tuesday, August 8, 2017. To participate by telephone, please dial 303-8028 or 536-5167.

















                                                    BRIEF-Chemocentryx says Avacopan safe and well tolerated at ERA-EDTA congress
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    7:54 AM ET 06/06/2017
                                                


Chemocentryx Inc (CCXI). * Oral presentations at ERA-EDTA congress highlight fourth potential indication for Avacopan and potential for CCR2 inhibition in focal segmental glomerulosclerosis. * Chemocentryx Inc (CCXI) says Avacopan appeared to be safe and well tolerated Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:

















                                                    Oral Presentations at ERA-EDTA Congress Highlight Fourth Potential Indication for Avacopan and Potential for CCR2 Inhibition in Focal Segmental Glomerulosclerosis (FSGS)
                                                


                                                    GlobeNewswire – 
                                                    7:30 AM ET 06/06/2017
                                                


-- Clinical Study Shows Drop in Proteinuria in Patients Treated with Avacopan for IgA Nephropathy -- -- Potential of CCR2 Inhibitor as a Therapeutic Treatment Option for FSGS Validated -- ChemoCentryx, Inc. (CCXI), a biopharmaceutical company developing new medications targeted at inflammatory and autoimmune diseases and cancer, announced today the findings of two studies presented during the 54th Eur...

















                                                    ChemoCentryx to Present at Two Upcoming Investor Conferences
                                                


                                                    GlobeNewswire – 
                                                    8:30 AM ET 05/24/2017
                                                


ChemoCentryx, Inc. (CCXI), a biopharmaceutical company developing new medications targeted at inflammatory and autoimmune diseases and cancer, announced today that Thomas J. Schall, Ph.D., President and Chief Executive Officer, will present at two upcoming investor conferences: A live audio webcast of the presentation at the Jefferies Healthcare Conference can be accessed through the Investors section...

















                                                    BRIEF-Chemocentryx says granted EU orphan drug designation for avacopan in treating patients with C3G
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    8:46 AM ET 05/23/2017
                                                


Chemocentryx Inc (CCXI). * Says granted EU orphan drug designation for avacopan in treatment of debilitating kidney disease C3 glomerulopathy. * Says plans to initiate a multi-center clinical endpoint study of avacopan for treatment of c3g in mid-2017 Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:

















                                                    ChemoCentryx Granted EU Orphan Drug Designation for Avacopan in the Treatment of Debilitating Kidney Disease C3 Glomerulopathy (C3G)
                                                


                                                    GlobeNewswire – 
                                                    8:30 AM ET 05/23/2017
                                                


ChemoCentryx, Inc. (CCXI), a biopharmaceutical company developing new medications targeted at inflammatory and autoimmune diseases and cancer, announced today that the European Medicines Agency has granted orphan medicinal product designation for avacopan in the treatment of patients with C3 glomerulopathy.

















                                                    BRIEF-Chemocentryx Q1 revenue $8.2 million
                                                


                                                    Reuters – 
                                                    5:08 PM ET 05/10/2017
                                                


Chemocentryx Inc (CCXI). * Chemocentryx (CCXI) reports first quarter 2017 financial results. * Q1 revenue $8.2 million. * Chemocentryx Inc (CCXI)- Expects to utilize cash and cash equivalents between $50 million and $55 million in 2017. * Chemocentryx Inc (CCXI) - Qtrly basic and diluted net loss per share $ 0.12 Source text for Eikon: Further company coverage:

















